<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="407" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
Lectotype by subsequent designation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurent, RF" journalOrPublisher="Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="65 - 96" refId="B113" refString="Laurent, RF, 1961. Note sur les Hyperolius et quelques Afrixalus (Salientia) du Musee de Berlin. Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 64 (1-2): 65 - 96" title="Note sur les Hyperolius et quelques Afrixalus (Salientia) du Musee de Berlin." volume="64" year="1961">Laurent (1961</bibRefCitation>
: 73). 
<bibRefCitation author="Fretey, T" journalOrPublisher="Alytes" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="11 - 26" refId="B59" refString="Fretey, T, Dubois, A, Ohler, A, 2014. The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina. Alytes 30: 11 - 26" title="The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina." volume="30" year="2014">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Frétey">Fretey</normalizedToken>
et al. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
corrected the type locality to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Douala”">&quot;Douala&quot;</normalizedToken>
based on an account and a map of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Buchholz’">Buchholz'</normalizedToken>
Central African travels provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Heinersdorff, C" journalOrPublisher="Edition Doerfler, Nebel Verlag, Utting" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B90" refString="Heinersdorff, C, 1880. Reinhold Buchholz' Reisen in West-Afrika nach seinen hinterlassenen Tagebuechern und Briefen nebst einem Lebensabriss des Verstorbenen. F. A. Brockhaus, Leipzig, [viii + (2)] 263 pp. [map.]" title="Reinhold Buchholz' Reisen in West-Afrika nach seinen hinterlassenen Tagebuechern und Briefen nebst einem Lebensabriss des Verstorbenen. F. A. Brockhaus, Leipzig, [viii + (2)] 263 pp. [map.]" year="1880">Heinersdorff (1880)</bibRefCitation>
. According to the latter, Buchholz visited 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Cameroons”">&quot;Cameroons&quot;</normalizedToken>
between October 1872 and August 1874. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Fretey, T" journalOrPublisher="Alytes" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="11 - 26" refId="B59" refString="Fretey, T, Dubois, A, Ohler, A, 2014. The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina. Alytes 30: 11 - 26" title="The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina." volume="30" year="2014">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Frétey">Fretey</normalizedToken>
et al. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
the collection in RMNH holds four additional paralectotypes (RMNH RENA 1788 A-D) from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Boutry”">&quot;Boutry&quot;</normalizedToken>
, coll. Pel (not listed by Gasso Miracle et al. 2007). Drawing in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1515/9783111625430-fm" author="Ahl, E" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B9" refString="Ahl, E, 1931b. Amphibia, Anura III, Polypedatidae. In: Hesse R (Ed.) Das Tierreich. Eine Zusammenstellung und Kennzeichnung der rezenten Tierformen. 55. Lieferung. Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co. Berlin und Leipzig, 477 pp. [+ (1-2)]. https://doi.org/10.1515/9783111625430-fm" title="Amphibia, Anura III, Polypedatidae. In: Hesse R (Ed.) Das Tierreich. Eine Zusammenstellung und Kennzeichnung der rezenten Tierformen. 55. Lieferung. Walter de Gruyter &amp; Co. Berlin und Leipzig, 477 pp. [+ (1 - 2)]." url="https://doi.org/10.1515/9783111625430-fm" year="1931 b">Ahl (1931b</bibRefCitation>
: 354, fig. 229) figuring paralectotype ZMB 4489. For the origin, history and status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1875" class="Reptilia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperolius guttatus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Hyperolius guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and drawings, photographs and redescriptions of the ZMB type specimens we refer to the revision by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fretey, T" journalOrPublisher="Alytes" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="11 - 26" refId="B59" refString="Fretey, T, Dubois, A, Ohler, A, 2014. The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina. Alytes 30: 11 - 26" title="The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina." volume="30" year="2014">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Frétey">Fretey</normalizedToken>
et al. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
The Berlin ornithologist Reichenow travelled together with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lühder">Luehder</normalizedToken>
and Buchholz from spring 1872 on a one year collecting trip to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Akkrá”">&quot;Akkra&quot;</normalizedToken>
on the Gold Coast [Accra, Ghana] and the region around 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Camaroons”">&quot;Camaroons&quot;</normalizedToken>
[Douala Region, Cameroon] (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02004082" author="Reichenow, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal fuer Ornithologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="353 - 388" refId="B174" refString="Reichenow, A, 1874. Zur Vogelfauna Westafrika's. Ergebnisse einer Reise nach Guinea. Journal fuer Ornithologie 22 (128): 353 - 388, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02004082" title="Zur Vogelfauna Westafrika's. Ergebnisse einer Reise nach Guinea." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02004082" volume="22" year="1874">Reichenow 1874</bibRefCitation>
; Heinersdorf 1880; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weidmann, C" journalOrPublisher="Bernhard Noehring, Luebeck, (9)" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B224" refString="Weidmann, C, 1894. Deutsche Maenner in Afrika - Lexicon der hervorragendsten deutschen Afrika-Forscher, Missionare etc. Bernhard Noehring, Luebeck, (9)" title="Deutsche Maenner in Afrika - Lexicon der hervorragendsten deutschen Afrika-Forscher, Missionare etc." year="1894">Weidmann 1894</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" author="Stresemann, E" journalOrPublisher="Journal fuer Ornithologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="111 - 120" refId="B208" refString="Stresemann, E, 1943. Anton Reichenow. 1. VIII. 1847-6. VII. 1941. Journal fuer Ornithologie 91 (1): 111 - 120, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" title="Anton Reichenow. 1. VIII. 1847 - 6. VII. 1941." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" volume="91" year="1943">Stresemann 1943</bibRefCitation>
; see also remarks on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buchholz &amp; Peters in Peters" authorityYear="1875" class="Reptilia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperolius acutirostris" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutirostris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Hyperolius acutirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Reichenow was assistant in the fish and reptile department in ZMB until Wilhelm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Peters’">Peters'</normalizedToken>
death. From 1883 he worked as an administrator and assistant in the mammal and reptile department. In 1888 he became curator for the reptile, bird and mammal exhibition in the new ZMB building on the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ivalidenstraße">Ivalidenstrasse</normalizedToken>
. After the retirement of his father-in-law Jean Louis Bennoit Cabanis in 1892, and after almost twenty years conducting various activities at ZMB, Reichenow took over as the curator of the ornithological collection (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" author="Stresemann, E" journalOrPublisher="Journal fuer Ornithologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="111 - 120" refId="B208" refString="Stresemann, E, 1943. Anton Reichenow. 1. VIII. 1847-6. VII. 1941. Journal fuer Ornithologie 91 (1): 111 - 120, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" title="Anton Reichenow. 1. VIII. 1847 - 6. VII. 1941." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" volume="91" year="1943">Stresemann 1943</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
